FIG. 3 is an enlarged sectional view of a fuel inlet end of the assembly showing installation of fuel heaters, a temperature sensor, and a water sensor;


FIG. 4 is an end plan view of the inlet end of the pump;


FIGS. 5A and 5B are respective plan and elevational views of a PTC heater used to heat the fuel;


FIG. 6 is a sectional view of a valve member of the pump illustrating electrical wiring connections to the thermal switch and one of the heaters;


FIGS. 7A and 7B are a respective plan view and an elevational view, in section, of a second method of mounting a heater to the valve member; and,


FIG. 8 is a schematic illustrating operation of the heaters.
